DATA CLOUD
Segment Time Zone

Your Data Cloud org sets the publish time zones on the initial segment save and segment canvas. Segment and activation fields display the Publish Schedule Start Date and Time in the user's time zone.

Updates made to your Salesforce org’s time zone aren’t reflected in existing segments.

EXAMPLE You schedule your segment publish start time for 1:00 PM EST with a time interval of 24 hours and then change your Salesforce org time zone to PST. The publishing time is 10:00 AM PST, not 1:00 PM PST. The absolute publish time doesn’t change because you changed your time zones.

Newly created segments follow the updated time zone. To update the time zone of an existing segment, resave the segment.

Segment publish is scheduled based on a time interval (12 or 24 hours) rather than a specific date and time. Therefore, a segment publish time doesn’t adjust for DST.
